We  recommended that Management:

Require every Department/Office of the City to prepare the PPMP containing all the information outlined in Section 7.3.2 of the RIRR of RA 9184, and submit the same to the City Budget Office for evaluation and inclusion in the budget proposal to be approved by the City Mayor;

After the Budget approval, require the CBO to furnish the BAC Secretariat of a copy of the budget proposals as well as the corresponding PPMPs for review and consolidation into the proposed APP;

Submit the adjusted PPMP to the BAC, through its Secretariat, for finalization of the modes of procurement under the proposed APP.

We recommended that Management maximize the utilization of the tobacco excise tax fund by implementing programmed projects that are envisioned to help in the attainment of:
Increase productivity, guarantee the market and as a whole increase farmer's income;
Development of alternative farming systems;
Management and subsequent ownership of these projects such as post harvest and secondary processing and by-product utilization; and
Infrastructure projects such as farm-to-market roads.  Also, strict adherence with the provisions of the Republic Act 7171 pertaining to charges from the Tobacco Excise Tax fund.

